# Project Context for Cursor — Hardik Verma Portfolio

## What This Is
A clone of the award-winning [oryzo.ai](https://oryzo.ai) website — a premium WebGL/Three.js product showcase built by Lusion design studio. The goal is to repurpose it as **Hardik Verma's personal developer portfolio**.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Astro (static site generator)
- **3D Engine**: Three.js + Gaussian Splatting (`.sog` files) via a custom WebGL engine
- **Styling**: Single CSS file at `public/_astro/index.css`
- **JS**: One monolithic bundle at `public/_astro/main.js` (do NOT edit this — it's the compiled 3D engine)
- **Workers**: `public/_astro/SplatsWorker.js` + `public/_astro/splat_sorter_bg.wasm` (Gaussian splat sorting — do NOT touch)

## Project Structure
```
src/
  layouts/Layout.astro        ← HTML shell, loads CSS + main.js
  pages/index.astro           ← ALL page content lives here
  components/                 ← Section components (Hero, Features, etc.)
    Header.astro
    Hero.astro
    Ai.astro
    Features.astro
    Grip.astro
    OpenWeight.astro
    Product.astro
    Sentiment.astro
    SocialContent.astro
    Sustainability.astro
    Testimonies.astro
    Wearable.astro

public/
  _astro/main.js              ← Compiled 3D engine (DO NOT EDIT)
  _astro/index.css            ← All styles
  images/                     ← Static images used in social/wearable sections
    social-content/           ← 9 webp images (lifestyle/product shots)
    testimonies/              ← 5 webp images (fake testimonials)
    video_thumb.webp
    wearable-gallery/         ← Gallery images + 2 mp4 videos
  models/                     ← 3D .buf files (DO NOT REPLACE — custom format)
  textures/                   ← WebP/PNG textures for 3D models
  fonts/                      ← Literata.woff2, DM-Mono-400-Latin.woff2
  splats/                     ← Gaussian splat files (props.sog, table_reflection.sog)
  rive/oryzo.riv              ← Rive animation file
```

## Critical Rule
**Do not edit `public/_astro/main.js`** or any file in `public/_astro/`. The 3D engine is a compiled black box. All text, nav, and content changes go in `src/` only. The JS engine reads DOM element IDs and class names — if you rename HTML elements, test that the 3D scene still works.

## What the Site Looks Like (Section by Section)
The site is a single long scrolling page with these sections in order:

1. **Hero** — Giant "ORYZO" text, 3D cork coaster on a desk with stationery, tagline "MADE FOR MARKETS. BUILT FOR MICROSECONDS.", nav bar (OVERVIEW / CAPABILITIES / INTEGRATIONS / CONTACT), video play button bottom right
2. **Intro** — "ISN'T JUST A DASHBOARD" with coaster floating on dark bg, description text right side
3. **AI Section** — "Powered by AI*" heading, coaster held in hand, colorful glow bg, "SENTIENT-1" label
4. **Wearable Gallery** — "SO LIGHTWEIGHT, it's wearable" with scrolling image gallery of lifestyle photos
5. **Features (Table scene)** — 3D desk/table scene, features cycle through: "ELEVATE YOUR COFFEE EXPERIENCE", "THERMODYNAMIC STABILITY", "PERFECTLY ROUND SERIOUSLY", "SMART FLIP" with descriptions
6. **Sustainability** — Giant "sustainability" text with bark/wood 3D texture close-up
7. **Integrations/Drop Test** — "3090 Drop Test" scrolling text, stats
8. **Product Selector** — "CHOOSE YOUR OWN ORYZO" with 3 tier selector (ORYZO / ORYZO PRO / ORYZO PRO MAX)
9. **Contact/Footer** — "WE CAUGHT YOUR ATTENTION WITH A NON-EXISTENT PRODUCT. IF WE CAN SELL A COASTER, IMAGINE WHAT WE CAN DO FOR YOUR BRAND." + Lusion branding + email signup

## The Goal
Transform this from an Oryzo product site into **Hardik Verma's personal developer portfolio**. Keep all 3D visuals and animations — only change text, nav labels, images in `public/images/`, and branding.

