## Images to Replace
The images in `public/images/social-content/` and `public/images/testimonies/` and `public/images/wearable-gallery/` are lifestyle/product photos. These can be replaced with:
- Screenshots of your projects (star-map visualiser, e-commerce dashboard)
- A headshot
- Any dev/work photos

Replace by swapping files with the **same filename and format** (webp preferred) so the JS engine finds them.

## What NOT to Change
- Any element `id` or `class` that the 3D engine uses to position/animate things
- The 3D model files in `public/models/` and `public/splats/`
- The Rive animation at `public/rive/oryzo.riv` (it's baked)
- Anything in `public/_astro/`
- Font files (the fonts work well for a portfolio)

## Current State
- Site is fully working locally (GitHub Codespaces, port 4321)
- `public/scripts/` contains Wakaru-decompiled JS chunks — these are NOT wired up and can be ignored. The working JS is `public/_astro/main.js`
- Layout.astro correctly loads `/_astro/main.js` and `/_astro/index.css`
- All fingerprint hashes have been removed from asset filenames and internal references updated
